						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1350 (1428 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Registers gift of a gold <hi rend="italic">kalaśa</hi> to god Raṅga by <hi rend="bold">Periyaperumāḷ,</hi> the sister of <hi rend="bold">Chakrarāya.</hi><note n="328-3">The remarks against this number in the Report state that the sister's name is not given. Female names having Perumāḷ as their part are not unknown.</note>The record is dated by the chronogram <hi rend="italic">Atmālōka</hi>—<hi rend="bold">Śaka 1350,</hi> <hi rend="bold">KIlaka, ba. 12, Wednesday, Uttiram</hi> which correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1428, October 6 Wednesday; ·21; ·89.</hi> The month was <hi rend="bold">Tulā.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
